About Me

I am currently a 3rd year Physics student with a minor in Computer Science and Economics at the Univeristy of Windsor.


In my Physics research position supervised by Dr. Rangan, we work on evaluting the interaction between light and matter at the nanoscale and the control of this interaction. I have led teams in creating Python programming projects for research purposes. Currently working on learning and applying my knowledge in programming quantum computers.


In my Chemistry reserach position supervised by Dr. Trant, we are currently working on design and synthesis of multifunctional nanocomposites for biological imaging.


In my free time, I volunteer at Newton's Taekwon-do as a 2nd degree black belt. I developed effective interpersonal and communication skills through leading group trainings, various open houses and events.

) } export default about
